                                                            <div class="article-item">
                                                                The study investigated the effectiveness of Facebook as a tool for information 
                                                                service delivery (ISD) in libraries. The descriptive survey method was adopted for the study which was 
                                                                based on the perceptual experience of 49 University of Benin Library staff who had Facebook accounts 
                                                                and took part in the library's Facebook group activities. The closed-ended questionnaire with a 4-point 
                                                                rating scale was used for data collection, and data analysis was by simple percentage. The results 
                                                                revealed that Facebook is an effective tool for ISD. Conclusively, the study provides an understanding 
                                                                of how libraries could use Facebook for ISD.
