                                                            <div class="article-item article-item-left text-muted">Description</div>
                                                            <div class="article-item">
                                                            The emergence of information and communication technologies posed a great deal of threat to library 
                                                            patronage. Hence, adopting new ways of doing old things became imperative for the survival of libraries 
                                                            and the profession of librarians. To achieve the aim of this study, the documentary study method was 
                                                            used to critically review the concept of embedded librarianship, its benefits, and its associated 
                                                            problems. Findings revealed that when librarians embed in the spaces of users, instead of waiting for 
                                                            the users to come over to the library, the impact of the services rendered to the user in their space 
                                                            is of greater significance when compared with the same service rendered in the library. Therefore, 
                                                            embedded librarianship is paramount in the survival of libraries and the library profession in an era of 
                                                            information technology influx.

